The paper proposes a self-attention-based autoregressive model for images and other high dimensional tensors. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the expressiveness of the model, which suggests it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which could place it in the computational linguistics (cs.CL) category. Finally, the paper discusses the computational requirements of the model, which could place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
